line_1: I rents me a nice little farm;
line_2: On Mondays I dresses me warm.

line_1: On Mondays I dresses me warm.
line_2: I rents me a nice little farm;
For we has a club in the town.

line_1: For we has a club in the town.
I only but wish ye could hear;
line_2: Ye niver heard nothing sae queer.

line_1: Ye niver heard nothing sae queer.
line_2: I only but wish ye could hear;

line_1: And stamps with his fit on the ground;
line_2: O lozes o' me! what a sound!

line_1: O lozes o' me! what a sound!
line_2: And stamps with his fit on the ground;

line_1: And spreads out his little black fist;
line_2: Ye niver seed yen sae distrest.

line_1: Ye niver seed yen sae distrest.
line_2: And spreads out his little black fist;

line_1: I hates for to hear a man cry;
line_2: To see if lal Juliet be by.

line_1: To see if lal Juliet be by.
line_2: I hates for to hear a man cry;

line_1: And speaks 'at ye hardly can hear;
line_2: And owther says Hinney or Dear.

line_1: And owther says Hinney or Dear.
line_2: And speaks 'at ye hardly can hear;

line_1: May he live a' the days of his life;
line_2: And may he ay maister his wife!
